{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L8HuAFH84UiejecX1Ag1xY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI found the exact issue you're looking for. Here's a complete breakdown of the code related to the \"project page workflow view\" where clicking on steps shows filename but doesn't load file contents:\n\n### The Issue (Issue ID: cloche-m8u)\n\nIn the project page workflow view, clicking on a step shows the filename of the prompt file or script file, but doesn't actually load and display the file contents.\n\n### Key Code Files\n\n1. **Frontend Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n   - Lines 251-284: The `openDrawer()` function that handles step clicks\n   - Lines 233: Step nodes use `onclick=\"openDrawer(...)\"` to open the drawer\n   - Lines 274-283: Fetches content from the API and displays it\n\n2. **Web Handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n   - Line 156: Route definition for the content endpoint\n   - Lines 1134-1199: `handleAPIStepContent()` function that serves the file contents\n   - Lines 1177-1196: Logic that reads prompt/script files from disk\n\n3. **CSS Styling**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n   - Lines 491-548: Drawer styling and layout\n\n### How the Workflow View Works\n\n1. **Displaying Steps** (project_detail.html, lines 228-237):\n   - Steps are rendered as SVG nodes in a DAG visualization\n   - Each step has an `onclick` handler that calls `openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)`\n\n2. **Opening the Drawer** (project_detail.html, lines 251-284):\n   - The drawer slides in from the right (CSS class `.drawer-open`)\n   - Initial drawer body shows basic step info (type, results, config keys) using hardcoded strings\n   - Then it fetches content from `/api/projects/{projectLabel}/workflows/{workflowName}/steps/{stepName}/content`\n   - Displays the loaded content in a `<pre>` tag inside `drawer-body`\n\n3. **API Endpoint** (handler.go, lines 1134-1199):\n   - Resolves the project directory from the project label\n   - Finds the workflow file in `.cloche/*.cloche`\n   - Parses the workflow to extract step config\n   - Reads the referenced file based on config keys:\n     - `prompt`: reads the file at the path specified in config\n     - `script`: reads the file at the path specified in config\n     - `command`: displays the command string directly\n   - Returns the file contents as plain text\n\n### The Bug Location\n\nThe bug is in the frontend code at lines 274-283 of `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`:\n\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n    .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n    .then(function(text) {\n        var el = document.getElementById('drawer-content');\n        if (text) {\n            el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;') + '</pre>';\n        } else {\n            el.innerHTML = '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">No content available</p>';\n        }\n    });\n```\n\nThe issue is that the API endpoint returns the file contents correctly, but the frontend may not be properly displaying it, or there could be an issue with how the fetch is handling the response.\n\n### Related Code Structure\n\n- **Step Information Display** (lines 258-268): Shows type, results, and config values as definition list items\n- **Content Container** (line 269): `<div id=\"drawer-content\">` is where the loaded content should appear\n- **Drawer Container** (lines 41-47): The sliding drawer panel structure\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Frontend template with openDrawer logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Web handler with handleAPIStepContent endpoint\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS for drawer and UI styling\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Tests for the handler\n5. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go` - Additional handler tests"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8090209f00c3efbe (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56325\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 26911</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c346fded-e5bd-469d-af11-5003ae2a312d","uuid":"6e25d42e-b9c1-45a7-9ea2-72e4bc4a7ee3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find the code related to the \"project page workflow view\" where clicking on steps shows filename but doesn't load file contents. This is a Go project called Cloche. Look for:\n\n1. Any web UI / frontend code (templates, handlers, JavaScript)\n2. Code related to displaying workflow steps and their prompt/script files\n3. HTTP handlers for project pages or workflow views\n4. Any API endpoints that serve file contents\n\nSearch broadly - check for HTML templates, JS files, web handlers, and anything related to \"workflow view\", \"step\", \"prompt file\", \"script file\", \"file contents\". Look in cmd/, internal/, and any web/ or ui/ directories.\n\nBe very thorough - check all file types including .html, .js, .go, .tmpl, .css files.","agentId":"a8090209f00c3efbe","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI found the exact issue you're looking for. Here's a complete breakdown of the code related to the \"project page workflow view\" where clicking on steps shows filename but doesn't load file contents:\n\n### The Issue (Issue ID: cloche-m8u)\n\nIn the project page workflow view, clicking on a step shows the filename of the prompt file or script file, but doesn't actually load and display the file contents.\n\n### Key Code Files\n\n1. **Frontend Template**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n   - Lines 251-284: The `openDrawer()` function that handles step clicks\n   - Lines 233: Step nodes use `onclick=\"openDrawer(...)\"` to open the drawer\n   - Lines 274-283: Fetches content from the API and displays it\n\n2. **Web Handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n   - Line 156: Route definition for the content endpoint\n   - Lines 1134-1199: `handleAPIStepContent()` function that serves the file contents\n   - Lines 1177-1196: Logic that reads prompt/script files from disk\n\n3. **CSS Styling**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n   - Lines 491-548: Drawer styling and layout\n\n### How the Workflow View Works\n\n1. **Displaying Steps** (project_detail.html, lines 228-237):\n   - Steps are rendered as SVG nodes in a DAG visualization\n   - Each step has an `onclick` handler that calls `openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)`\n\n2. **Opening the Drawer** (project_detail.html, lines 251-284):\n   - The drawer slides in from the right (CSS class `.drawer-open`)\n   - Initial drawer body shows basic step info (type, results, config keys) using hardcoded strings\n   - Then it fetches content from `/api/projects/{projectLabel}/workflows/{workflowName}/steps/{stepName}/content`\n   - Displays the loaded content in a `<pre>` tag inside `drawer-body`\n\n3. **API Endpoint** (handler.go, lines 1134-1199):\n   - Resolves the project directory from the project label\n   - Finds the workflow file in `.cloche/*.cloche`\n   - Parses the workflow to extract step config\n   - Reads the referenced file based on config keys:\n     - `prompt`: reads the file at the path specified in config\n     - `script`: reads the file at the path specified in config\n     - `command`: displays the command string directly\n   - Returns the file contents as plain text\n\n### The Bug Location\n\nThe bug is in the frontend code at lines 274-283 of `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`:\n\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n    .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n    .then(function(text) {\n        var el = document.getElementById('drawer-content');\n        if (text) {\n            el.innerHTML = '<pre>' + text.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;') + '</pre>';\n        } else {\n            el.innerHTML = '<p style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">No content available</p>';\n        }\n    });\n```\n\nThe issue is that the API endpoint returns the file contents correctly, but the frontend may not be properly displaying it, or there could be an issue with how the fetch is handling the response.\n\n### Related Code Structure\n\n- **Step Information Display** (lines 258-268): Shows type, results, and config values as definition list items\n- **Content Container** (line 269): `<div id=\"drawer-content\">` is where the loaded content should appear\n- **Drawer Container** (lines 41-47): The sliding drawer panel structure\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Frontend template with openDrawer logic\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Web handler with handleAPIStepContent endpoint\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS for drawer and UI styling\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Tests for the handler\n5. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go` - Additional handler tests"}],"totalDurationMs":26911,"totalTokens":56325,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":244,"cache_read_input_tokens":54965,"output_tokens":1114,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_