{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01YPA2vtm5gi8kX9cmZpySeh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly. Looking at the parser test:\n\n```go\nassert.Equal(t, `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")`, code.Config[\"prompt\"])\n```\n\nSo `step.Config[\"prompt\"]` stores the full value including `file(\"...\")` wrapper, e.g., `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")`.\n\nBut in the handler:\n\n```go\nif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, prompt))\n```\n\nIt's trying to read a file named `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` which of course doesn't exist! It needs to extract the path from the `file()` wrapper first.\n\n\nThere's also a mismatch where the DSL uses `run` for scripts, but the handler is checking for `command` and `script` keys instead. I need to verify both of these issues and then fix them, plus check what the API returns to the frontend to understand the full data flow.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3889,"cache_read_input_tokens":24219,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3889},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c346fded-e5bd-469d-af11-5003ae2a312d","uuid":"4f47f5cb-f762-400c-92af-71ae1cb3b574"}
